This paper deals with image quality assessment, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) is also a key aspect of the proposed method, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves regression analysis to map extracted features to quality predictions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with multi-scale and multi-layer features, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
